    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "DIRECTOR, FBI",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "SAC, KNOXVILLE",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "VITAL FACILITIES",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "NATIONAL MILITARY ESTABLISHMENT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "(Unknown Object Over Oak Ridge, Tennessee,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "3/2/50; [REDACTED] - COMPLAINANT).",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "Re Knoxville teletype to Bureau, Attention Mr. [REDACTED] dated",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "March 1, 1950, entitled \"Unknown Object Over Oak Ridge, 3/1/50;",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "COMPLAINANT.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "Referenced teletype advised that the reliability of [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "complainant in this matter, had been questioned and the efficiency of his radar",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "equipment placed in some doubt. It is felt advisable, however, to apprise the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "Bureau of all matters in connection with this incident.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "At 11:15 P. M. on March 1, 1950, Mr. [REDACTED], owner and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "operator of [REDACTED], Knoxville, telephonically communicated with this office",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "advising that he had",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "detected on his privately owned radar equipment an indication of what he be-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "lieved to be an object circling at an altitude of 40,000 feet over Oak Ridge,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Tennessee. At approximately 11:25 P. M. on this date, this information was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "made available by me to Mr. [REDACTED], Security Division, Atomic Energy",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "Commission, Oak Ridge, for his information. Inasmuch as the matter was not",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "one wherein the Bureau had jurisdiction, no further action was taken.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "On the morning of March 2, 1950, Mr. [REDACTED] communicated with Third",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "Army authorities at Ft. McPherson, Georgia and the 14th U. S. Air Force at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "Greenville, South Carolina, at which time they were advised of the information",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "furnished by KNOX.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "At approximately 5:30 P. M. on March 2, 1950, a telephone call was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "received by me from Mr. [REDACTED] advising he had been talking with Captain [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "an assistant to Chief [REDACTED] of the AEC Security Patrol concerning the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "reported object over Oak Ridge, Tennessee. [REDACTED] further advised that his",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "equipment was surplus Army radar equipment bearing the designation AN/7 which",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "he himself had converted for acceptable use with his radio equipment. He",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "continued that he used this radar equipment to track airliners in and out and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "with this equipment he could distinguish between a DC-3 and a DC-4. He",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "stated he had again spotted the object at approximately 11:05 A. M. on March 2,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "1950 and he estimated it to be approximately twenty miles away at an altitude",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "of 100,000 feet and circling over Oak Ridge.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "status": "blank"
    },
